A morphone is the smallest unit of western music which has musical Morphones can be as small as a drum stroke, or as long as a musical Musicoherence and The Composer The Dynascore Composition Algorithm (aka The Composer) uses AI and high performance computing to break down a piece of music and reassemble its morphones in a way that maximizes the musicoherence Musicoherence means that the desired track length, transitions, pauses, and ending markers happen at the right time, and in the right order, while allowing the musical sequence to still sound like a coherent, custom It’s tricky business, but Dynascore magically Midisaurus The Composer’s output is a specialized MIDI file readable only by our Midisaurus feeds the MIDI to , who is almost always The magic of Dynascore is not just generating a composition that matches requirements - it’s also making it sound great to the human Once The Composer delivers a viable composition, it’s time to generate audio, and that’s where loads the virtual instruments specified by Midisaurus from among the vast Dynascore For each track in the MIDI, emulates the correct virtual instruments to produce a professional grade audio WAV RenderRoar Once the mix is complete, the audio file is then processed on our proprietary mastering

plates will carry the kelp deep under the crust of the Earth, removing the CO 2 from the biosphere for geologic This could also be done as part of the “last voyage” of each farm when it is at , so that each farm contributes to the cycle during its normal life and also contributes to removing fossil carbon out of the atmosphere at Discussion Water Cycle: Consider the water cycle often taught as part of grade school The sun evaporates water out of the ocean into the clouds and clouds drift over the The clouds then rain over the mountains and The water eventually make its way downstream and back into the ocean where it is once again evaporated, and the water cycle Carbon Cycle (see Fossil Carbon below): The carbon cycle is a similar cycle to the water The carbon is absorbed by plants and trees from the If people (consider the early pioneers) cut down the trees and burned them for heat, the carbon is released into the atmosphere where it is absorbed by the trees Eventually those same trees might be cut down again for Or the trees may live a full life, die of natural causes and The carbon escapes into the atmosphere where it is later by younger plants and Either way, whether the trees are deliberately burned or they slowly rot, these are both examples of carbon continuing through the In our kelp example, the carbon will be absorbed from the ocean by kelp on the ocean farms – considered Fossil Carbon: Fossil carbon comes from deep resources and includes oil and coal taken out of geologic When oil or coal is burned, it is not , because the carbon is newly introduced to the current geologic When fossil carbon is burned, it increases the balance of carbon in the atmosphere and overwhelms the ability of the modern environment to absorb Our oceans have been absorbing far more fossil carbon in recent years, which has been making the oceans warmer and more In addition to warmer oceans, we observe evidence that coral and shells have been damaged, and some have been severely Until we stop burning fossil fuels, the problem will get Sequester Carbon: One way to reduce the fossil carbon in the environment is to sequester the Marine BioEnergy has been asked, do our kelp farms sequester carbon? You can also schedule a call with an engineer if that s easier for We would love to learn about your and help you get Install Pyroscope Server # We provide a few different ways for you to install Pyroscope server: if you re on a Mac, we recommend using homebrew if you re on Linux, we recommend using our rpm or deb packages we also have a docker image that you can use anywhere To find out about other ways of installing Pyroscope, or to find packages for other CPU architectures (e.g ARM) visit our Downloads macOS Linux Docker Copy brew install brew pyroscope Verify the installation # After installing Pyroscope, verify that the installation worked by opening a new terminal session and running the command pyroscope . macOS Linux Docker Copy pyroscope You should see something like this: Copy _ __ _ _ _ __ ___ ___ ___ ___ _ __ ___ | _ \| | | | __ _ \ __| __ _ \| _ \ _ \ | |_) | |_| | | | (_) \__ \ (_| (_) | |_) | __ | \__, |_| \___ |___ \___\___ | \___| | | __ | | | |_| |___ |_| USAGE pyroscope [flags] <subcommand ... If something doesn t work, reach out to us in our slack group or email us at . Start the server # To start pyroscope server run pyroscope server command: macOS Linux Docker Copy pyroscope server Pyroscope server is the database where all the profiling information is It also has a web UI (by default available on port :4040 ) After you start the server you should be able to open http: localhost:4040 and see that pyroscope server is profiling itself ( application). Profile your applications # Now that you have pyroscope server running you can start continuously profiling your own We currently support 3 platforms: Ruby Python Go We ll be adding more platforms soon, if you want us to prioritize one particular platform, reach out to us in our slack group or email us at . Ruby Python Go To start profiling a Ruby application, add pyroscope exec before the For example, if you re working with a Rails application, here s how you profile it: Copy export PYROSCOPE_SPY_NAME = rbspy export PYROSCOPE_APPLICATION_NAME = pyroscope exec rails server If you re running your app inside a Docker container, see our Docker Guide . We also have examples . This will make pyroscope agent send profiling data over to pyroscope Open http: localhost:4040 in your browser to explore the incoming profiling Configuration # Pyroscope can be configured with command line arguments, environment variables and config See Configuration for more info on this Deploy Pyroscope in production # If you re installing pyroscope in production environment, read Deployment Guide . Below we’ll explore the components of geographically targeted landing pages and why Geo Landing Pages is the best tool to help bring qualified customers and clients to your What are geo landing pages and how do they help with local marketing? To put it simply, a geo landing page is essentially built for companies or websites that work or serve clients or customers in multiple Similarly, it could be of greater use for shops with multiple franchises, each present in a different The purpose of a unique landing page is to help customers in finding a store present within their For instance, think about a local coffee It might be located in just one state, but it might also have franchises in other cities or countries across the So, to make sure that it shows up in the search results for one particular area, the coffee shop should create a landing page for each individual The resulting page is thus what is called a page, and the aim is to attract people living within that particular Why geo landing pages should be a part of your local marketing campaign In , google updated its algorithm with a new feature referred to as Possum . This feature makes several changes to how local searches One of the key features of this update is that search results for locations that are close to the actual searched for are being displayed in higher So, city or town based search results are not limited to the city only, but also include businesses and services in nearby localities ranked highly in the search Furthermore, searchers who are conducting a local search are more likely to be interested in the proximity of a business more than the brand name, professionalism, expertise, While these other factors are also important, the physical proximity takes Therefore, Google filters out the results based on how close a business is to the searcher’s physical As a result, your business is likelier to get higher rankings if it’s close to the customer, and the customer is also more likely to become a potential lead and then a Therefore, it is important to create landing pages, so your customer gets specified content and entry to your What features make up a geo landing page? An important reason why GEO SEO and landing pages have become so popular recently is that studies and Google’s own research shows that over % of the searches conducted on Google are done for local This means that users search for local results and are likelier to click on the results that are specific or at least closer to their To make sure that people come across your page, geo landing pages should include the following: Title tags & Meta Descriptions Just like with regular SEO, title tags and meta descriptions for pages should contain the name of the service or Along with that, they should mention the location of the For example, if you want to make a geo landing page for a “leg pain doctor,” then you should also add in the area you are Resultantly, the final title tag would become “leg pain doctor South El ” This is one of the best practices and promises to deliver excellent Header 1 or H1 In most cases, SEO practices dictate that H1 or the first header should be similar to the title Continuing the example stated above, the H1 tag would be “Leg Pain Doctor South El ” Header 2 or H2 The usual practice is to include more keywords in the second This is where most SEO professionals They fail to fully utilize their However, to make sure that your geo landing page generates more leads, make sure to mention what you are offering in the H2 So in our case, the H2 could be “searching for a leg pain doctor near South El Monte?” Relevant content pertaining to the location This is where geo landing pages differ from regular SEO The latter only includes the most generalized content, which not only seems bland but also can get flagged by google as duplicate It is essential to include content that reflects and informs people about the location and services you are For example, if we consider our leg pain doctor example, it would be great to mention nearby hospitals and leg pain You could go one step further and also include additional facts about your Advisory Board January , January , by Molly Stone Valeria Coscia, , Bill DuBay, , Paul Evans, and Mike Wittmann, will strategically advise Benuvia Manufacturing, a growing, privately held ROUND ROCK, January , – Benuvia Manufacturing, Inc, a leading CDMO providing small molecule active pharmaceutical ingredients, formulation and drug product manufacturing from preclinical to commercial scale, today announced the formation and appointment of its Senior Advisory The members of the Senior Advisory Board bring more than years of pharmaceutical and business Valeria Coscia, , Bill DuBay, , Paul Evans and Mike Wittmann, bring a wide variety of expertise and talent to this inaugural Coscia, an independent consultant in the Pharma industry, has over years of experience with broad responsibilities in multiple functional areas including research & development, portfolio management, GMP manufacturing and CMC regulatory Prior to her work as an independent consultant, Coscia was Vice President R&D and Chief Technology Officer for Noramco DuBay, global head of R&D for SK Pharmteco, has more than years of experience in pharmaceutical research and Prior to his current position, DuBay served as Vice President R&D for AMPAC fine chemicals where he was responsible for developing the product pipeline, API manufacturing, and API Evans, Vice President Global Business Development and Portfolio with Pharmascience, , brings years of experience as an executive in the pharmaceutical space, spanning both generic and specialty pharma and Prior to joining the Pharmascience, , he held senior roles at Johnson Matthew Teva USA, Qualitest Pharmaceuticals, Alita Pharmaceuticals and Wittmann is the Chair of the Department of Marketing, Industrial Distribution, and Economics in the Collat School of Business at the University of Alabama at Prior to joining the UAB faculty, he served as Chair of the Marketing and Merchandising Department at The University of Southern Wittmann has worked as a marketing strategy consultant with a diverse group of companies ranging from startups to Fortune 1,000 “I am so pleased to have this talent join Benuvia ” said Scott Watson, President of Benuvia “As a growing privately held company, having advisors of this caliber, is I am grateful for their commitment to our ” The goal of the Senior Advisory Board is to provide strategic and technical advice to the Benuvia Manufacturing Leadership Team and to help Benuvia Manufacturing become a premier integrated pharmaceutical CDMO . Benuvia Ma nufacturing Commercial Operations Benuvia Manufacturing operates over ,000 square feet of research, development, and manufacturing space in its cGMP facility located in Round Rock, The manufacturing facility received its Type II Drug Master File (32552) from the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) in to produce pharmaceutical grade pure quality Today, Round Rock is the only CBD active pharmaceutical ingredient (API) contract manufacturing site in the producing an FDA approved cannabinoid The facility is a DEA and FDA registered production site and is fully regulated and compliant with DEA, EPA, and OSHA Benuvia Manufacturing also manufacturers SYNDROS® (dronabinol), a prescription medicine approved by the FDA for the treatment of nausea and vomiting caused by medicine (chemotherapy) in patients who have failed to respond adequately to conventional antiemetic treatments and anorexia associated weight loss in patients with AIDS (Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome). Benuvia Manufacturing offers a comprehensive suite of solutions for pharmaceutical, biotechnology, and consumer product companies to achieve their development and commercial needs: Drug product manufacturing and small molecule active pharmaceutical ingredient – and cGMP from grams to commercial metric ton scale Preclinical and clinical drug product formulations Quality assurance and validation Analytical services Drug development including custom synthesis About Benuvia Manufacturing, Benuvia Manufacturing, is a privately held contract manufacturing organization that develops and manufactures active pharmaceutical ingredients and For more information visit . Pricing Resources Blog FAQ About Us Reviews Career Media Contact Get Started How to Spot Credit Repair Scams There are many things credit repair companies are not allowed to do or promise If it sounds like it’s too good to be true, it probably is, and you should steer clear of that Here is a list of signs that you should look out for that may be a red flag that a company is not Company claims Guaranteed Results Under the Credit Repair Organizations Act (CROA), credit repair companies cannot guarantee Here are a few common examples of false promises unethical credit repair companies might make: Improvement to your credit score Results in a fixed time period Removal of all of negative items, even if they are accurate Upfront Payment is Requested The CROA prohibits credit repair companies from asking for any payment before they provide any Many scammers know that most consumers don’t know this and, as a result, promise a quick turnaround on credit repair for a large upfront Again, if it sounds to good to be true, it probably Claims a New Identity is Needed A credit repair company can’t promise or offer you a new Anyone offering you a new identity is a Besides guaranteeing results, scammers may try to promise you a clean slate with a new Employer Identification Number (EIN) or a Credit Privacy Number (CPN). They tell you to use these numbers on your future credit applications instead of your Social Security We explain more about common credit repair scams Don’t Explain Your Legal Rights Credit repair companies should explain your legal rights to you from the These are a few common things an unethical credit repair company might Tells you not to contact the credit bureaus directly Doesn’t give you a copy of the contract to review before signing Fails to inform you that you can repair your credit yourself without the help of a credit repair company Leaves out important information from the contract, like the date services will be executed or that amount you will pay If you feel like the company isn’t telling you everything or refusing to answer your questions, you should seek services Asks You to Misrepresent Information Finally, an unlawful credit repair company might ask you to misrepresent your This can range from unlawfully using an EIN or CPN number in place of your social security number to claim you are a victim of identity theft when you’re Any of these sound familiar? We can help you repair your credit the right Contact us CALL or GET STARTED What to Do If You Are Scammed There are a few things you can do if you realize you’ve fallen victim to a credit repair Take a look at your options Report the organization to your state attorney general File a complaint with the Federal Trade Commission and the Better Business Bureau Consult with an attorney if you’d like to take further legal action How to Safely Repair Your Credit Making payments on time and disputing inaccurate or duplicate information on your credit reports can help you repair your While you can do this on your own, US Allied Financial will make the process easier and more US Allied Financial proudly adheres to CROA to make sure we give our clients the best experience We’ve helped clients challenge information that is unfair, inaccurate and Give us a call today so you can start on the path of better credit!
